    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-udon-broth/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until browned, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-udon-broth/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>pak choi</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Chop the base off the <strong>pak choi</strong> and discard, then slice in half lengthways</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-udon-broth/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has browned, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add your <strong>honey</strong> and <strong>half</strong> your <strong>soy sauce</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 4-5 min or until the mince becomes crispy, sticky and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy chilli mince</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-udon-broth/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince is cooking, dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>sriracha</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and <strong>remaining soy sauce </strong>in<strong> </strong>600ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[800ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1L] </span><strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> spicy stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-udon-broth/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>pak choi</strong> and <strong>spicy</strong> <strong>stock</strong> and cook for 2-3 min until the pak choi has started to soften</p><p>Stir through your <strong>udon noodles</strong> and cook for 1 min further \u2013 this is your <strong>udon broth</strong></p><p>Tip: You may need to gently break apart the noodles with a fork!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-udon-broth/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel lengths from your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> until you have a pile of carrot ribbons</p><p>Trim and finely slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-udon-broth/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> udon broth</strong> topped with the <strong>crispy chilli mince</strong>, <strong>carrot ribbons </strong>and <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame seeds </strong>and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
